As a junior at Jesuit High School in Dallas, Jordan Spieth wrote the letter to the Murphy family who funded the scholarship that helped pay for his tuition .
As he stepped off the final green he embraced, in turn, his father Shawn, his college sweetheart Annie, his brother Steven, his grandfather and various friends .
Spieth was already dreaming of winning the Masters at Augusta National .
'He's just a class guy in every way and it's difficult not to root for him,' said Phil Mickelson .